<HEADLINE>  Liberty's Lobo Hurts Knee in Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Rebecca Lobo, the New York Liberty's leading  
rebounder, injured her left knee in the second minute of Thursday 
night's WNBA season opener against Cleveland at Madison Square 
Garden. 
</P>
<P>
	She left the game at 18:58 with Cleveland leading 2-0. She was  
expected to have an MRI Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Lobo grabbed a rebound after Kym Hampton's missed shot, pivoted  
and fell to the floor in pain. Play continued about 30 seconds 
while she was on the floor under the Liberty basket before an 
official's timeout. 
</P>
<P>
	Lobo averaged 11.7 points and 6.9 rebounds last season.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
