<HEADLINE> Spalding To Cut Jobs at N.Y. Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICOPEE, Mass. (AP) -- Spalding Sports Worldwide says more than  
120 jobs are being eliminated at its Gloversville, N.Y., plant. 
</P>
<P>
	Vaughn Rist, vice president for human resources, said Thursday  
the Chicopee-based sporting goods company plans to reduce costs by 
contracting out some of the golf club assembly work that had been 
done in Gloversville. 
</P>
<P>
	Assembly of its high-end Top-Flite clubs is being moved to its  
Chicopee plant, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The company will continue to make golf balls in Gloversville as  
well as Chicopee, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Spalding currently employs about 1,000 people in Chicopee, and  
about 200 in Gloversville. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
