<HEADLINE> Pavarotti Nervous About Lebanon Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) -- Luciano Pavarotti says he is nervous  
about performing for the first time before an audience in the 
Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
	The Italian tenor is scheduled to give a two-hour concert at a  
stadium here Saturday in what organizers have billed as a 
``historic event'' to mark the country's emergence from the 1975-90 
civil war. 
</P>
<P>
	``I tell you, I will be afraid just like the first time I sang  
April 29, 1961,'' Pavarotti told reporters. 
</P>
<P>
	When asked why he had chosen to perform in Beirut, he said: ``Is  
there a reason why I should not? I've been treated like a king, 
flown in on a beautiful, sumptuous plane and surrounded by 
beautiful women.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Organizers estimate that 18,000 people will attend the two-day  
concert. Ticket prices range between $35 to $300 -- about 50 percent 
more than the minimum monthly salary here. Proceeds will go to 
charity. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
