<HEADLINE> Lachemann To Be US Pitching Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Former Angels manager Marcel Lachemann was hired  
Thursday as pitching coach for the United States at this summer's 
Pan Am Games, the qualifying tournament for the 2000 Sydney 
Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
	Lachemann, a minor league coordinator for Anaheim, replaces Dave  
Wallace, hired Saturday as pitching coach of the New York Mets. 
</P>
<P>
	Former Detroit Tigers manager Buddy Bell will manage the U.S.  
team at the tournament, which runs from July 24-Aug. 2 at Winnipeg, 
Manitoba. Professionals are eligible for Olympic baseball for the 
first time, but major league baseball is making available only 
players not on 40-man rosters. 
</P>
<P>
	Lachemann, 57, was the Angels' manager from 1994-96, and was a  
pitching coach for the team from 1984-92 and 1997-98. 
  	   	
</P>
