<HEADLINE> Blue Jays' Green Returns to Lineup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Toronto Blue Jay center fielder Shawn Green  
returned to the starting lineup Friday night against the 
Philadelphia Phillies after missing most of two weeks because of an 
injured left wrist. 
</P>
<P>
	Green sustained a fracture when he was hit by New York Yankees  
pitcher Andy Pettitte on May 28. Despite the injury, Green did not 
spend any time on the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	He started against the Montreal Expos on June 4 but left after  
four innings due to soreness in the wrist. Five days later, he made 
an appearance as a pinch runner against the New York Mets. 
</P>
<P>
	Green, tied for second in the American League with 33 extra-base  
hits and tied for fifth with 23 multihit games, batted third 
against the Phillies. 
</P>
<P>
	``He hit early today and said he felt fine,'' Toronto manager  
Jim Fregosi said. ``He has to expect some soreness and stuff.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Green was hitting .322 with 15 homers and 48 RBIs before the  
injury. 
</P>
<P>
	``I hope he can play through it and be productive at the same  
time,'' Fregosi said. ``I told him not to expect miracles.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Green had played in a team-high 155 consecutive games before  
missing a start on May 29 against the Yankees. 
  	   	
</P>
