<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Stocks Close Higher / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The yen gained moderately against the dollar in  
Tokyo today, boosted by signs of revival in the Japanese economy. 
Stocks also edged up. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 118.66 yen today, down 0.46 yen from late  
Thursday in Tokyo and below its late New York level of 118.84 yen 
overnight. The greenback ranged between 118.60 yen and 119.09 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The gains for the yen came after the Economic Planning Agency's  
announcement Thursday that Japan's economy grew 1.9 percent, or 7.9 
percent on an annualized basis, in the first quarter of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	The numbers marked Japan's first expansion after five quarters  
of contraction. The country is struggling with its deepest 
recession since the end of World War II. 
</P>
<P>
	``There has been a shift in sentiment regarding the Japanese  
economy,'' said Ken Landon, senior currency strategist at Deutsche 
Bank in Tokyo. ``The change in pace is quite dramatic ... and 
people are starting to wake up to that fact.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Currency traders also said they were assessing what the  
yen-selling action by the Bank of Japan on Thursday afternoon means 
for the market's mid-term direction. The intervention followed the 
announcement of new GDP figures. 
</P>
<P>
	Japanese officials recently have expressed dissatisfaction with  
dollar-yen volatility. The greenback was worth more than 122 yen at 
the beginning of this month, but then dropped as low as 117.63 yen 
after the release of Thursday's economic data. 
</P>
<P>
	According to a market estimate, the Bank of Japan spent about  
dlrs 1 billion in the intervention Thursday, the Nihon Keizai 
newspaper said. The central bank last intervened on Jan. 12 in 
Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks also benefited from the signs of economic growth.  
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 95.93  
points, or 0.56 percent, to close at 17,198.55. On Thursday, the 
average finished up 480.12 points, or 2.89 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section closed up 13.07 points, or 0.96 percent, at 1,380.68 
points. The TOPIX was up 25.10 points, or 1.87 percent, on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Overseas money came in pretty actively today,'' said Chuck  
Lambert, a market analyst at Jardine Fleming Securities. ``Things 
may have bottomed out and are turning around.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered retreaters 696 to 526, while 102  
issues were unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
	First Section volume was estimated at 1.66 billion shares,  
inflated by the settlement of June futures and options contracts, 
which did not seem to have a major impact on prices. On Thursday, 
volume was 713 million shares. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies today, the euro was traded at 124.70 yen,  
down from 125.11 yen late Thursday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark No. 213 10-year Japanese government bond rose to  
1.7000 percent from Thursday's finish of 1.5900 percent, driving 
its price down to 97.43 yen from 98.36 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
