<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rookie Zonta Returns After Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTREAL (AP) -- Riccardo Zonta is trying very hard not to show  
his impatience. 
</P>
<P>
	When the 23-year-old Brazilian drove onto Circuit Gilles  
Villeneuve today at the start of practice for the Canadian Grand 
Prix, it was a resumption of a budding Formula One career that was 
suspended when he crashed hard in Brazil during practice for the 
second race of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	So far, Zonta's F1 resume shows only a non-finish in the  
season-opener in Australia because of a gearbox failure. 
</P>
<P>
	But at least the cast is off his mending right ankle after a  
month of hampered mobility. 
</P>
<P>
	``The biggest problem now is when I stop walking and stand on  
the foot,'' Zonta said Thursday as his team prepared his 
BAR-Supertec race car nearby. ``When I am in the car, with the foot 
out in front of me, no problem.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Zonta, a test driver for Team McLaren last year and the FIA  
Grand Touring Champion, said he wasn't deterred by the first injury 
of his racing career -- but he was frustrated. 
</P>
<P>
	``I wanted to get back into the car sooner than this,'' he said.  
``I wanted to come back (last month) in Monaco, but the doctor said 
I had to be able to jump on one foot and I wasn't ready for that, 
yet. 
</P>
<P>
	``They said I wasn't ready yet for Barcelona (two weeks ago),  
but I thought I was.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Until today, his only time in the cockpit of his BAR ride since  
the accident was last week in Silverstone, England. But even that 
was very dissatisfying. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was set and I only got five laps,'' Zonta said with a  
smile. ``That was not enough to tell me much.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Fortunately for the youngster, his gear shift lever is on the  
steering wheel. Unfortunately, he has had to adjust from 
right-footed breaking to the left foot. 
</P>
<P>
	``That is a big change, but I'm a professional race driver and I  
will get used to it,'' he said. ``Sometimes, you just have to 
adjust.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Veteran racer Mika Salo of Finland took Zonta's place for three  
races and managed finishes of seventh in San Marino and eighth in 
Spain -- the team best this season. Championship points are awarded 
only to the top six in each race. 
</P>
<P>
	BAR, in only its second season, also fields cars for local  
favorite Jacques Villeneuve. The former Indianapolis 500 winner and 
CART champion has had a season that may even be more frustrating 
than Zonta's. 
</P>
<P>
	Villeneuve, who was considered one of the top drivers in Formula  
One while racing for Team Williams in 1996 and 1997, has failed to 
finish in five starts this season. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mika is an experienced driver and I know he helped the team to  
grow up a lot,'' Zonta said. ``For me, it's difficult because this 
is my first race back. For Jacques, it's difficult because he needs 
to finish races and the team needs to score points. 
</P>
<P>
	``But we are working hard and getting stronger. We just have to  
finish races.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
