<HEADLINE> Brave Act Heads Shoemaker Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Brave Act, an impressive winner of the  
Inglewood Handicap last month, heads a field of nine entered in 
Sunday's $350,000 Shoemaker Breeders' Cup Mile at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Brave Act, a 5-year-old English-bred son of Persian Bold, will  
be ridden by Goncalino Almeida in the 56th running of the one-mile 
race for horses 3 and up on Hollywood Park's turf course. 
</P>
<P>
	Others entered are Ladies Din, who will be ridden by Kent  
Desormeaux; Indian Rocket, David Flores; Silic, Corey Nakatani; 
Fabulous Guy, Brice Blanc; Hawksley Hill, Alex Solis; Chullo, Chris 
McCarron; Lord Smith, Garrett Gomez; and Poteen, Eddie 
Delahoussaye. 
</P>
<P>
	All starters will carry 124 pounds. Ladies Din and Silic will  
run coupled in the wagering as an entry. 
</P>
<P>
	Brave Act has won five of his last seven races and 10 of 20  
lifetime starts with earnings of $724,130. He won the Inglewood 
Handicap on May 16 by 3 1/2 lengths over Lord Smith. 
</P>
<P>
	Hawksley Hill finished third in the race last spring, and second  
behind Da Hoss in the Breeders' Cup Mile in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to finishing second in the Inglewood race, Lord  
Smith has won four races and over $580,000 this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Ladies Din led all Southern California horses with six stakes  
victories last year. 
</P>
<P>
	A a field of nine headed by defending champion Budroyale was  
entered in the $125,000 Super Diamond Handicap, to be run earlier 
in the day. 
</P>
<P>
	Budroyale, a 6-year-old son of Cee's Tizzy who has won 14 of 38  
starts and $902,310, will be ridden by Gomez and carry 126 pounds 
in the 1 1-16 mile race for California-breds 3 and up. 
</P>
<P>
	Among others entered are Mateo, who will be ridden by Chris  
Antley and carry 121 pounds, and Busy Little Beaver, Flores, 118. 
  	   	
