<HEADLINE> Sharks Re-Signs Center Damphousse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- The San Jose Sharks on Friday re-signed  
center Vincent Damphousse, a late-season acquisition who helped the 
team reach the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal were not announced.  
</P>
<P>
	Damphousse, 31, was acquired from Montreal last season for  
several draft picks. He has 347 goals and 582 assists in his career 
and played in his 1,000th game with the Sharks on April 6. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, he had 19 goals and 30 assists in 77 games,  
including 12 games with San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
	``We saw what the addition of a a player of Vinnie's caliber  
meant to our team last season,'' general manager Dean Lombardi 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was a major factor in us making the playoffs and makes us  
stronger up the middle, is creative in the offensive zone and 
significantly upgrades our special teams,'' he added. 
</P>
<P>
	The seventh-seeded Sharks lost to Colorado in six games in the  
opening round of the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Damphousse, a two-time all-star, began his career with Toronto,  
playing there for five seasons, followed by a year in Edmonton and 
seven seasons with Montreal before being traded to San Jose. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
