<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Opens Fire in Michigan, 3 Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SOUTHFIELD, Mich. (AP) -- A gunman opened fire on his former  
psychiatrist Friday, killing the doctor and another person before 
fatally shooting himself, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Four other people were wounded in the shooting at the office of  
Dr. Reuven Bar-Levav, who died at his office on the 12th floor of 
an office building in this Detroit suburb. 
</P>
<P>
	The name of the gunman -- and the third victim slain, a woman  
from the Detroit area -- was being withheld. 
</P>
<P>
	``It appears we've got a doctor-patient relationship,'' Police  
Chief Joseph Thomas said. ``We are still trying to determine why it 
happened.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Southfield police Detective Darrel Palmer said it was believed  
the gunman was a former patient of Bar-Levav and that the shooting 
happened during ``some sort of meeting.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The victim's daughter, Dr. Leora Bar-Levav, a psychiatrist who  
practiced with her father, said the gunman was no longer a patient. 
</P>
<P>
	``He'd been seen very briefly last year,'' Leora Bar-Levav said  
from her home in Franklin. She declined to answer further 
questions. 
</P>
<P>
	Four victims were taken to a hospital. A man was in serious  
condition with a gunshot wound to the chest, and three other 
victims were being treated for less serious wounds they received 
after being shot at close range, Dr. Peter Goodman said. 
</P>
<P>
	The building -- an office complex with at least two dozen floors  
-- was evacuated of its visitors and workers. 
</P>
<P>
	Bar-Levav, a medical doctor and psychiatrist who shifted his  
practice to Southfield from Detroit a few years ago, has written at 
least two self-published books, the last a 1995 effort titled 
``Every Family Needs a CEO.'' Bar-Levav's other book is ``Sinking 
in the Shadow of Feeling.'' 
</P>
<P>
	According to the jacket of his 1995 book, Bar-Levav was born in  
1927 in Berlin, fled Nazi Germany with his family seven years later 
and went to what now is Israel. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
