<HEADLINE> Jays Send Quantrill to Syracuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Paul Quantrill, who has made five appearances  
during a rehabilitation assignment at Class-A Dunedin, was 
reassigned Friday to Triple-A Syracuse. 
</P>
<P>
	Quantrill, who remains on the disabled list, has not played in  
the major leagues since breaking his right leg in a snowmobile 
accident Jan. 6. He was 3-4 with seven saves and a 2.59 ERA in 82 
games last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Quantrill, 30, was 0-1 with a 4.50 ERA at Dunedin, allowing five  
hits in six innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Toronto also said it has signed four players selected in this  
year's amateur draft -- outfielder Michael Snyder (second round) and 
right-handers Brian Cardwell (fourth), David Hanson (sixth) and 
Jeremy Cook (24th). 
  	   	
