<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Media Ruling Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- In a June 10 story about court action in a case  
involving NBC's ``Dateline'' show, The Associated Press erroneously 
reported that the segment in question was about the Louisiana state 
police. 
</P>
<P>
	The court case centers on whether NBC has to hand over a  
videotape made for a segment that showed a Calcasieu Parish 
sheriff's deputy stopping a car. The network was investigating 
whether law enforcement officials were making decisions based on 
race, nationality or out-of-state plates. 
</P>
<P>
	The 2nd U.S. Court of Appeals had ruled in September that NBC  
had to hand the tape over to lawyers for a Hispanic couple who are 
suing the deputy, alleging civil rights violations. The June 9 
story reported that the court had set aside that ruling, saying it 
may need to rehear that issue. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
