<DOCNO> APW19990611.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-11 20:20:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Top News at 11 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Russian Troops Are in Kosovo  
</P>
<P>
	PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) -- A convoy of up to 300 Russian  
soldiers rolled into the Kosovo capital of Pristina early Saturday 
to the cheering of Serb crowds, the force apparently defying what 
NATO said was an understanding that Russia not enter the province 
alone. Hours before NATO was to send its own peacekeepers into 
Kosovo, Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov said the Russian 
troops had been ordered to leave. But the Russians moved to the 
outskirts of Pristina and stopped for the night. At Stenkovec, 
Macedonia, about 400 British tanks and fighting vehicles were 
revving up and awaiting the order to move into Kosovo. 

</P>
<P>
	U.S., Russians Hold Troop Talks  
</P>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- Negotiators struggled Saturday to hammer out a  
compromise on how Russian troops will work with NATO peacekeepers 
in Kosovo as a column of Russian soldiers entered the province 
ahead of the alliance's forces. The ITAR-Tass news agency, 
reporting from Belgrade, said that the Russian Defense Ministry had 
made the decision to send its troops ahead of NATO peacekeepers. It 
said the move had been coordinated with the Yugoslav army supreme 
command. It was not clear whether the Russian Foreign Ministry knew 
in advance of the military's plans. 

</P>
<P>
	Albright Tours Refugee Camp  
</P>
<P>
	SKOPJE, Macedonia (AP) -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright  
assured ethnic Albanian refugees that NATO peacekeepers in Kosovo 
would help them return home ``to live a decent, normal life.'' 
Albright declared Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic and the 
Serbs have given up control of Kosovo. ``All the world knows about 
your suffering,'' she assured them. As Albright toured the 
Stenkovic camp, NATO troops made preparations to move into Kosovo 
to protect the returning ethnic Albanians. The deployments could 
begin Saturday. 

</P>
