<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tyson Gets OK To Train in Arizona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The welcome mat is out for Mike Tyson.  
</P>
<P>
	The former heavyweight champion was granted permission to train  
in Arizona for a fight in Nevada, possibly in August, officials in 
Arizona and Maryland confirmed Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm sure he's looking forward to getting back into training  
and boxing,'' said Paul Kemp, a lawyer for Tyson. 
</P>
<P>
	Kemp said he does not know when Tyson plans to leave for  
Arizona. He must arrive at least by Monday, when he is to report to 
the Maricopa County Adult Probation Department in Phoenix, said 
John MacDonald, communications officer for the Arizona Supreme 
Court. 
</P>
<P>
	No matter to Ricky Ricardo, who helps run the downtown Phoenix  
gym where Tyson trains. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're already putting up a banner that says ``Welcome Back to  
The Community, Mike Tyson,'' he told The Arizona Republic on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyson, who was released last month and will be on probation  
until February, pleaded no contest to misdemeanor assault charges 
that stemmed from a fender bender in Gaithersburg, Md., last 
August. Tyson will continue with anger management counseling, as 
well as meeting his community service requirements, while in 
Arizona, Maryland corrections officials said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	The boxer last fought in Jan. 16 and was behind on all three  
cards before he knocked out Francois Botha in the fifth round at 
Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyson also served three years in Indiana on a rape conviction.  
He registered in Arizona as a sex offender last fall when he 
decided to make Phoenix his home. He also has a home with his wife 
in Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
	Ricardo's father, Richard Rodriquez, who also helps run the  
Phoenix gym, said he has an extra reason for welcoming Tyson. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyson put up money to enable the gym to remain in operation,  
Rodriquez said. It serves about 60 amateurs. 
</P>
<P>
	``He kept me alive,'' Rodriquez said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
