<HEADLINE> Dodgers Bring Up Hot Hitter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Los Angeles Dodgers purchased the  
contract of outfielder Brent Cookson from their Triple A farm club 
Friday and designated infielder Chance Sanford for assignment. 
</P>
<P>
	Cookson hit .335 with 18 homers and 48 RBIs in 55 games for  
Albuquerque of the Pacific Coast League this season. He signed a 
minor league contract with the Dodgers last January. 
</P>
<P>
	Cookson, 29, played in 22 games for the Kansas City Royals in  
1995 -- his only stint in the big leagues -- and hit .143 with five 
RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	Sanford, 27, had two hits in eight at-bats and two RBIs for the  
Dodgers after having his contract purchased from Albuquerque on 
June 4. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dodgers also announced they have agreed to terms with  
outfielder Shane Victorino of St. Anthony High in Wailuku, Hawaii. 
Victorino was the team's sixth-round selection in this year's 
amateur free agent draft. 
  	   	
