<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Lower; Dow Down 130.76  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell sharply today, extending a dismal  
week on Wall Street, as investors became increasingly certain that 
the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates to slow down the 
robust U.S. economy. While fears about a rate increase have shaken 
stocks for weeks, rumors that the Fed would boost rates higher or 
sooner than previously thought sent the market sliding in afternoon 
trading. The Dow Jones industrial average was down 130.76 at 
10,490.51. The blue-chip index fell 309.33 points, or 2.9 percent, 
for the week. Broader stock indicators also fell, with the 
technology-dominated Nasdaq composite index down 37.06 points to 
2,447.56. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,490.51 - 130.76
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1268  Declines 1681  Unchgd  578
