<HEADLINE> Lawyer Sentenced in Drug Laundering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- A lawyer was sentenced to five years in prison  
Friday for laundering money on behalf of Colombian drug kingpins 
who were his clients. 
</P>
<P>
	William Moran was convicted last summer along with Michael  
Abbell, a former Justice Department extradition expert. His 
sentencing was delayed. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors said the lawyers went beyond just zealously  
representing their clients, members of the now-defunct Cali drug 
cartel, and actually took part in their crimes by transferring 
money to jailed cartel members and their families. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorneys said Moran and Abbell may have acted  
unethically, but they in no way helped the cartel run its drug 
smuggling business. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, the judge overturned a racketeering conspiracy  
conviction against Abbell and Moran, agreeing they did not take 
part in drug smuggling. 
</P>
<P>
	Four other lawyers indicted in the case have pleaded guilty to  
lesser charges. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
